                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/3821: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dennis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-09-24T10:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1926—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. After two days conference with me Liberal junta informs me it desires to
                    attend conference on the basis of the Department’s telegram of September 11, 1
                    p.m., authorizing my good offices, and is sending a mission of Federico Sacasa,
                    Mariano Arguello, Benjamin Abaunza to Guatemala to talk with Juan B.
                    Sacasa.mission should leave in a day or two and conference be possible first or
                    second week October. … It is clear now Liberals have poor military leaders and
                    organization and resumption of hostilities would probably result in further
                    useless disaster for them and country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dennis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
